Free agent transactions that occurred after May 12 , 2015 did not impact the team 's formula for determining compensatory selections for the 2016 draft .
JOSH GORDON 'S REINSTATEMENT AND REHAB Section::::Josh Gordon 's reinstatement and rehab .
On April 1 , wide receiver Josh Gordon applied for reinstatement following an indefinite suspension by the NFL due to repeated violations of the league 's substance abuse policy , causing him to miss the entire 2015 season .
On April 11 , it was revealed that Gordon had failed another drug test , and on April 12 , the league announced that Gordon 's appeal had been denied .
He was eligible to reapply on August 1 .
On July 25 , the NFL announced that Gordon would be reinstated on a conditional basis , and can stay with the team during a four - game ban to begin the season .
